# Conda Environment Activation

Before running any shell command that requires Python tooling (linters, formatters, test runners, package managers, etc.), activate the conda environment specified in `.cursor/.cursorenv`.

Use this activation prefix for all such commands:

```bash
eval "$(/opt/miniconda3/condabin/conda shell.zsh hook)" && conda activate lincapps && <your command>
```

If `.cursor/.cursorenv` is absent or unreadable, fall back to running commands without activation and note the issue to the user.
